Abstract: Internet-Drafts are draft documents valid for a maximum of six months and may be updated, replaced, or obsoleted by other documents at any time. It is inappropriate to use Internet-Drafts as reference material or to cite them other than as "work in progress." Abstract Integrated Services in the Internet is rapidly becoming a reality. Meanwhile, ATM technology is appearing in the marketplace. It is an important problem to integrate ATM networks into this emerging Integrated Services Internet. "Classical" IP over ATM[11, 8] is now widely deployed, effectively solving the problem of "best effort service" in internets with ATM links. A key remaining issue is to provide the Internet Integrated Services (IIS) model over internets with ATM links. This draft provides guidelines for using ATM VCs with QoS as part of an Integrated Services Internet.
